1
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:12,074
Delicious Vegan Sausages, Cheese
and Burgers - Vegusto.co.uk

2
00:01:41,120 --> 00:01:43,240
Scared the living crap out of me.

3
00:01:43,520 --> 00:01:45,280
Meryl Streep she wasn't.

4
00:01:45,440 --> 00:01:47,000
Who's Meryl Streep?

5
00:01:47,200 --> 00:01:49,960
Zoe, she's like Katie Holmes
to our parents.

6
00:01:50,200 --> 00:01:52,520
So, what's next, ladies?

7
00:01:52,760 --> 00:01:54,320
-I have to go home.
-No.

8
00:01:54,520 --> 00:01:58,920
I can't have another fight with
my parents. They think I'm in bed.

9
00:01:59,800 --> 00:02:01,320
Were you kids in bed early?

10
00:02:01,560 --> 00:02:04,640
-I stayed up till 1 0.
-After 9, Rhett was asleep.

11
00:02:04,840 --> 00:02:06,520
-Who's driving them?
-I will.

12
00:02:06,720 --> 00:02:09,800
Nicki's selling coffee at school,
I'm helping her.

13
00:02:11,560 --> 00:02:12,600
It sucks.

14
00:02:12,840 --> 00:02:15,840
Do not say "sucks," say "disappoints."

15
00:02:19,200 --> 00:02:21,720
I don't need a lunch.
I'll go with Tash.

16
00:02:21,960 --> 00:02:24,640
Eat pizza three days in a row?
I think not.

17
00:02:24,840 --> 00:02:26,720
That's really good.

18
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:29,240
The proportions are perfect...

19
00:02:29,440 --> 00:02:31,960
...but do you draw
what you really see?

20
00:02:32,480 --> 00:02:36,640
The simplest is the hardest.
Seeing what's in front of you.

21
00:02:48,920 --> 00:02:50,520
What's on for tonight?

22
00:02:50,760 --> 00:02:54,920
I am so grounded. I got busted
sneaking back inside last night.

23
00:02:55,200 --> 00:02:58,880
-Damn, how'd you manage that?
-My dad set the motion detector.

24
00:02:59,160 --> 00:03:02,200
Our parents are getting
paranoid in their old age.

25
00:03:02,400 --> 00:03:04,320
Mine still trust me.

26
00:03:07,640 --> 00:03:09,320
It's beautiful.

27
00:03:11,520 --> 00:03:13,560
Not a bad couple of decades.

28
00:03:13,760 --> 00:03:16,280
Better than the first two
without you.

29
00:03:16,480 --> 00:03:18,840
To 20 years of you and me.

30
00:03:23,040 --> 00:03:25,760
And to our children, safe at home.

31
00:03:33,560 --> 00:03:35,000
Hey, cool, you lost them!

32
00:03:35,200 --> 00:03:37,120
Macho Mustang boys, to boot!

33
00:03:38,200 --> 00:03:41,760
-We struck a blow for sisterhood!
-The only "blow" you know.

34
00:03:42,120 --> 00:03:43,480
Diss.

35
00:03:44,360 --> 00:03:46,680
-Any raves?
-Full Moon Underground.

36
00:03:46,880 --> 00:03:49,600
San Bernardino.
Probably Saturday.

37
00:03:49,800 --> 00:03:52,000
I'll tell Mom I'm staying with you.

38
00:03:52,280 --> 00:03:55,080
I can't believe you
still work that scam.

39
00:03:55,400 --> 00:03:57,800
What can I say?
My 'rents are clueless.

40
00:04:00,360 --> 00:04:02,600
I'll bring glowsticks if you buy gas.

41
00:04:02,880 --> 00:04:06,440
-That's such a good idea!
-Nice try, Beams.

42
00:04:06,680 --> 00:04:08,680
Rest, it'll be one hell of a weekend.

43
00:04:08,960 --> 00:04:12,120
-Bye, Tasha.
-Don't let the bedbugs bite!

44
00:04:17,120 --> 00:04:18,560
Hasta!

45
00:04:35,400 --> 00:04:37,240
Now they call the cops on me.

46
00:04:46,560 --> 00:04:47,840
Hello!

47
00:04:53,120 --> 00:04:54,520
Hello!

48
00:04:55,800 --> 00:04:57,600
I'm sorry I'm late.

49
00:04:58,400 --> 00:04:59,840
Ruby Baker?

50
00:05:02,040 --> 00:05:03,840
Yeah, I'm Ruby.

51
00:05:06,360 --> 00:05:10,280
Whatever they said, I'm not missing.
I just went out.

52
00:05:11,800 --> 00:05:13,560
Your parents were in a car accident.

53
00:05:14,360 --> 00:05:15,840
Are they okay?

54
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:20,440
-Ruby, why don't you have a seat, hon?
-Are they okay?

55
00:05:20,800 --> 00:05:24,000
My partner will help you have a seat.
Ruby.

56
00:05:24,320 --> 00:05:26,040
-I can sit down myself.
-I know.

57
00:05:26,240 --> 00:05:27,160
Are they okay?

58
00:05:27,360 --> 00:05:29,280
-Relax.
-We're here to help you.

59
00:05:30,360 --> 00:05:31,560
You'll be okay.

60
00:05:31,840 --> 00:05:33,760
Relax. Ruby?

61
00:05:38,440 --> 00:05:39,400
Ruby.

62
00:05:40,000 --> 00:05:41,000
You'll be okay.

63
00:05:41,280 --> 00:05:43,800
-Get her pulse.
-Can you hear me, Ruby?

64
00:05:48,800 --> 00:05:50,440
"They are as asleep.

65
00:05:50,720 --> 00:05:53,880
In the morning, they're like grass
which groweth up.

66
00:05:54,080 --> 00:05:56,960
In the morning, it flourisheth
and groweth up.

67
00:05:57,160 --> 00:06:00,640
In the evening, it is cut down
and withereth...

68
00:06:00,920 --> 00:06:05,320
...for we're consumed by thine anger
and by thy wrath we're troubled.

69
00:06:05,760 --> 00:06:09,480
Thou has set our iniquities
before thee, our secret sins...

70
00:06:09,760 --> 00:06:12,000
...in the light of thy countenance.

71
00:06:12,280 --> 00:06:15,680
For all our days are
passed away in thy wrath.

72
00:06:15,960 --> 00:06:18,600
We spend our years as
a tale that is told...

73
00:06:18,880 --> 00:06:21,400
...so teach us to number our days...

74
00:06:21,600 --> 00:06:25,240
...that we may apply
our hearts unto wisdom."

75
00:06:25,440 --> 00:06:29,120
I think Rhett Baker wants to
say something. Rhett?

76
00:06:45,880 --> 00:06:47,400
I just--

77
00:06:50,400 --> 00:06:52,360
I just wanna say....

78
00:07:01,440 --> 00:07:02,440
I just....

79
00:07:03,160 --> 00:07:04,280
It's okay.

80
00:07:10,720 --> 00:07:14,400
I didn't work with Dave and Grace
or see them every day...

81
00:07:14,760 --> 00:07:16,960
...but I knew them for 1 0 years...

82
00:07:17,320 --> 00:07:19,880
...and I'm sure if they
could hear this....

83
00:07:22,400 --> 00:07:23,640
Well, Grace...

84
00:07:24,280 --> 00:07:27,160
...would do her dismissive
little giggle.

85
00:07:28,160 --> 00:07:29,560
You know the one.

86
00:07:30,080 --> 00:07:33,760
And Dave would mutter
an "expletive deleted."

87
00:07:38,040 --> 00:07:40,680
They'd hate to be remembered
as anything but...

88
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:42,280
...ordinary.

89
00:07:44,440 --> 00:07:46,720
Which is exactly what they were:

90
00:07:47,680 --> 00:07:49,400
Anything but ordinary.

91
00:07:51,960 --> 00:07:53,600
But they will live on...

92
00:07:54,560 --> 00:07:58,520
...through their children
and in all our hearts.

93
00:08:03,720 --> 00:08:04,760
Ruby?

94
00:08:06,400 --> 00:08:07,880
Do you remember me?

95
00:08:08,840 --> 00:08:11,040
I'm Uncle Jack,
your mom's brother.

96
00:08:11,680 --> 00:08:13,640
I'll go wait by the car, okay?

97
00:08:16,920 --> 00:08:20,000
If there's anything that you need...

98
00:08:20,280 --> 00:08:21,960
...anything I can do...

99
00:08:22,400 --> 00:08:27,040
...l don't mean in the next few weeks
or months, I mean anytime.

100
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:31,640
How come I haven't seen you
in, like, 1 0 years?

101
00:08:32,160 --> 00:08:34,240
Have you even met my brother Rhett?

102
00:08:35,040 --> 00:08:36,680
Well, of course I have.

103
00:08:37,400 --> 00:08:39,600
I haven't seen either of you in years.

104
00:08:39,840 --> 00:08:43,360
First of all, I live pretty far away.
Chicago.

105
00:08:43,840 --> 00:08:45,440
Then how will you help us?

106
00:08:46,400 --> 00:08:49,520
I don't know.
There's the phone, e-mail.

107
00:08:50,160 --> 00:08:53,920
-You and my mom never wrote.
-That's true.

108
00:08:54,280 --> 00:08:57,240
As siblings get older,
they go separate ways.

109
00:08:57,480 --> 00:09:00,120
-You and Rhett are close now--
-We're not.

110
00:09:01,160 --> 00:09:03,480
We have nothing in common.

111
00:09:04,640 --> 00:09:08,120
Used to feel that way about your mom.
It's not true.

112
00:09:08,640 --> 00:09:12,760
I used to think I'd take a month off
and come out here...

113
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:17,160
...and get to know you,
your brother and Grace again.

114
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:20,760
Nice to see you.
Sorry things didn't work out.

115
00:09:29,320 --> 00:09:31,800
-I'll call you later, okay?
-Okay.

116
00:09:52,680 --> 00:09:55,000
Ruby? Hi.

117
00:09:56,240 --> 00:09:59,160
-I'm Alvin Begleiter.
-Hi.

118
00:09:59,720 --> 00:10:01,640
I'm so sorry.

119
00:10:02,440 --> 00:10:06,840
I'm your--
I was your parents' estate lawyer.

120
00:10:07,640 --> 00:10:09,280
I planned their wills...

121
00:10:09,880 --> 00:10:13,320
...what they wanted to do
with their money and--

122
00:10:15,360 --> 00:10:20,240
The most important issue right now
is who'll take care of you.

123
00:10:20,480 --> 00:10:21,680
You and Rhett.

124
00:10:21,920 --> 00:10:24,400
I'm assuming you know the Glasses?

125
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:27,280
I've known them my whole life.

126
00:10:27,960 --> 00:10:30,120
Good. I know that your parents...

127
00:10:30,400 --> 00:10:33,960
...chose them after a great deal
of consideration.

128
00:10:34,240 --> 00:10:36,120
And there's something else.

129
00:10:36,320 --> 00:10:39,520
Your parents were extremely thrifty...

130
00:10:39,800 --> 00:10:44,640
...and with your mom's share,
your dad's life insurance...

131
00:10:46,240 --> 00:10:51,000
...there's enough for you
and Rhett for the rest of your lives.

132
00:10:51,240 --> 00:10:53,320
Obviously you don't know Rhett.

133
00:10:55,680 --> 00:10:58,920
That's good.
I'll give you one of my cards.

134
00:10:59,200 --> 00:11:01,240
I don't expect trouble.

135
00:11:01,480 --> 00:11:06,240
But if you have any concerns,
any problems....

136
00:11:06,400 --> 00:11:09,600
I'm an estate lawyer
and also a trust lawyer.

137
00:11:09,880 --> 00:11:13,600
I want to be someone you can trust.

138
00:11:18,880 --> 00:11:21,440
-You call me, okay?
-Okay.

139
00:11:22,040 --> 00:11:23,640
Mr. Glass.

140
00:11:27,840 --> 00:11:30,120
-Ruby.
-Thank you.

141
00:11:31,840 --> 00:11:35,080
My mom and dad would've
loved that speech.

142
00:11:36,640 --> 00:11:39,000
-They would've loved it.
-Come here.

143
00:11:42,200 --> 00:11:46,600
That's good.
We're gonna get through this.

144
00:11:46,880 --> 00:11:49,240
We'll get through it together, okay?

145
00:11:54,400 --> 00:11:56,200
Oh, Ruby.

146
00:11:56,680 --> 00:11:58,440
You're in good hands.

147
00:12:26,720 --> 00:12:27,720
Hey!

148
00:12:28,800 --> 00:12:33,400
-You guys ready for Malibu?
-It'll be a change, we won't lie.

149
00:12:33,600 --> 00:12:35,200
It's not the worst place.

150
00:12:35,400 --> 00:12:40,000
-Is this your car?
-My company's, on loan for today.

151
00:13:26,240 --> 00:13:27,640
Sweet!

152
00:13:30,240 --> 00:13:32,200
This place is huge!

153
00:13:36,440 --> 00:13:38,720
Hey, Rubes, check out this view.

154
00:13:39,040 --> 00:13:41,760
Yeah, it's pretty amazing.

155
00:13:46,680 --> 00:13:50,200
-Cool, a meteorite!
-It's art, Rhett.

156
00:13:51,360 --> 00:13:54,600
Give them the tour.
Stall them, I'll order dinner.

157
00:13:54,880 --> 00:13:57,000
Let's get the lay of the land.

158
00:14:02,120 --> 00:14:04,040
Master suite.

159
00:14:05,320 --> 00:14:06,600
Home gym.

160
00:14:08,800 --> 00:14:11,400
-Home theater.
-Sweet.

161
00:14:11,680 --> 00:14:14,400
-You never have to leave home.
-If only.

162
00:14:15,560 --> 00:14:17,560
Vicki comes in most days.

163
00:14:17,800 --> 00:14:19,360
-Hola, ninos.
-Hola.

164
00:14:19,560 --> 00:14:20,640
Hello!

165
00:14:23,240 --> 00:14:25,120
This is your room.

166
00:14:26,880 --> 00:14:29,440
It's temporary quarters, of course.

167
00:14:30,360 --> 00:14:35,040
Unpack, get settled,
and I'll meet you in the kitchen.

168
00:14:38,040 --> 00:14:40,160
We're sharing a room?

169
00:14:44,640 --> 00:14:48,320
Glance at me when I'm changing
and you're busted.

170
00:14:49,120 --> 00:14:53,760
We have a little calamari,
a little risotto with mushrooms...

171
00:14:54,880 --> 00:14:58,240
...and green salad with
some Swiss chard.

172
00:15:04,640 --> 00:15:08,280
-Do you have any Garfield?
-What is that?

173
00:15:08,480 --> 00:15:12,360
-It's crap in a can.
-If it's crap, how come you eat it?

174
00:15:12,600 --> 00:15:17,080
-Come on, kids. Try the calamari.
-Isn't that squid?

175
00:15:22,600 --> 00:15:25,560
-Honey, tonight....
-I'll call Domino's.

176
00:15:27,040 --> 00:15:28,280
Thank you.

177
00:15:43,880 --> 00:15:46,040
Can you turn and face the wall?

178
00:15:47,400 --> 00:15:49,000
Who are you, the Blair Witch?

179
00:15:49,280 --> 00:15:51,680
I'm worse. Just face the wall.

180
00:15:52,960 --> 00:15:55,000
Turn that stupid thing off!

181
00:16:44,920 --> 00:16:47,640
There's public school,
then there's public school.

182
00:16:47,840 --> 00:16:50,680
Trust me, there won't be any
Bloods or Crips.

183
00:16:51,520 --> 00:16:53,800
I'm not scared of getting gunned down.

184
00:16:54,080 --> 00:16:57,440
-You're a great kid--
-It's not about being great.

185
00:16:57,720 --> 00:17:00,280
-It's about being....
-New?

186
00:17:00,520 --> 00:17:01,600
Middle-of-the-year new.

187
00:17:03,360 --> 00:17:06,680
There's a saying we teach
the Pain Ward patients.

188
00:17:07,400 --> 00:17:09,560
"This too shall pass."

189
00:17:10,680 --> 00:17:13,920
This too shall pass.
This too shall pass.

190
00:17:17,280 --> 00:17:18,240
Hi.

191
00:17:18,520 --> 00:17:21,400
Why don't you take
a seat in the back?

192
00:17:31,040 --> 00:17:33,000
We have a new addition.

193
00:17:33,480 --> 00:17:36,200
Would you introduce yourself,
Miss Baker?

194
00:17:38,360 --> 00:17:39,680
You just did.

195
00:17:46,080 --> 00:17:47,320
Hi.

196
00:17:49,320 --> 00:17:51,000
I'm Ruby Baker.

197
00:17:53,640 --> 00:17:57,240
I used to go to Shady Lane.
That's in the Valley.

198
00:17:58,680 --> 00:18:01,160
Not my choice,
just an accident of birth.

199
00:18:03,240 --> 00:18:04,640
How come you moved here?

200
00:18:06,080 --> 00:18:08,280
It was another accident.

201
00:18:11,080 --> 00:18:13,080
Let's make Ruby feel welcome.

202
00:18:28,480 --> 00:18:29,560
Thanks for the lift.

203
00:18:32,800 --> 00:18:34,360
Sweet!

204
00:18:38,400 --> 00:18:40,520
I can't believe it!

205
00:18:40,800 --> 00:18:43,400
Like one of those isn't noisy enough?

206
00:18:43,680 --> 00:18:47,680
No, Rubes. You can't play
"Pokémon Snap" on PlayStation.

207
00:18:47,960 --> 00:18:50,920
You can play "Ape Escape,"
but not on N-64.

208
00:18:51,520 --> 00:18:53,600
Mom and Dad would freak out.

209
00:18:55,840 --> 00:18:57,080
Don't talk about them.

210
00:19:19,240 --> 00:19:22,200
I haven't seen one girl
with blue-black hair.

211
00:19:22,400 --> 00:19:26,720
The guys surf and swim all day.
That sun-worshiping culture.

212
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:28,200
That sounds hot.

213
00:19:28,480 --> 00:19:32,960
I checked my pager all day.
I figured you'd call and you didn't.

214
00:19:33,240 --> 00:19:37,440
Cell phones are banned at school.
The kids don't care.

215
00:19:37,640 --> 00:19:40,200
They can't see they
lost their liberties.

216
00:19:40,440 --> 00:19:43,520
They have so much sunstroke,
they're wasted.

217
00:19:44,120 --> 00:19:45,320
Ruby?

218
00:19:49,480 --> 00:19:52,920
I got us an assortment
of different things.

219
00:19:53,120 --> 00:19:56,000
Some cold pastas, some salads.

220
00:20:01,080 --> 00:20:05,920
Ruby, I think that you'd be
well-served by a better attitude.

221
00:20:11,240 --> 00:20:14,760
It's okay. I don't mind take-out.
You're busy.

222
00:20:15,040 --> 00:20:16,600
It's not from Wendy's.

223
00:20:16,840 --> 00:20:19,960
I meant your attitude
toward your new school.

224
00:20:22,720 --> 00:20:26,360
-My attitude?
-I overheard your conversation.

225
00:20:27,680 --> 00:20:28,920
You were listening in?

226
00:20:29,480 --> 00:20:33,960
No, I was trying to get a line out,
but that's beside the point.

227
00:20:34,240 --> 00:20:37,440
The point is, you need those
kids to like you.

228
00:20:37,640 --> 00:20:40,480
Otherwise, you'll isolate,
sabotage yourself.

229
00:20:40,680 --> 00:20:44,680
-You'll have a miserable time.
-Okay, I get it.

230
00:20:50,120 --> 00:20:51,400
I learned something.

231
00:20:59,720 --> 00:21:01,080
Ruby?

232
00:21:01,640 --> 00:21:02,880
Ruby.

233
00:21:03,800 --> 00:21:06,520
-Wake up.
-I'm awake.

234
00:21:08,600 --> 00:21:10,880
-Wake up.
-Mommy?

235
00:21:14,080 --> 00:21:15,480
Mommy?

236
00:22:22,880 --> 00:22:24,640
You scared the crap out of me.

237
00:22:25,920 --> 00:22:29,640
I heard noises. I thought
it was a burglar or coyote.

238
00:22:29,920 --> 00:22:31,640
I'm not used to kids here.

239
00:22:33,560 --> 00:22:34,520
Come here.

240
00:22:41,000 --> 00:22:42,240
Thank you.

241
00:22:53,160 --> 00:22:54,280
You must be freezing.

242
00:22:55,840 --> 00:23:00,200
No more 3 a.m. swims. With all
the glass, you hear everything.

243
00:23:00,520 --> 00:23:02,680
I'll set the alarm at night.

244
00:23:03,880 --> 00:23:04,920
Are you coming?

245
00:23:13,760 --> 00:23:16,120
Drunk driving among teens has...

246
00:23:16,360 --> 00:23:19,400
...steadily decreased,
but we can do better.

247
00:23:19,640 --> 00:23:21,440
As these images starkly attest...

248
00:23:22,200 --> 00:23:25,880
...alcohol remains the No. 1
problem among teens.

249
00:23:26,760 --> 00:23:30,240
This year, 20 percent
of teenage drivers....

250
00:23:54,400 --> 00:23:57,280
How was your first day
of Driver's Ed?

251
00:23:58,440 --> 00:24:02,840
-Fine, I guess.
-They still show gruesome movies?

252
00:24:03,040 --> 00:24:04,800
Those were the Dark Ages.

253
00:24:05,000 --> 00:24:08,360
They have better ways
of teaching kids today.

