Hi, you must be Rhett. I'm Nancy Ryan.

507
00:51:01,200 --> 00:51:02,520
Nice to meet you.

508
00:51:02,720 --> 00:51:06,080
So Rhett, how do you spend
your evenings?

509
00:51:06,680 --> 00:51:09,600
When I finish my homework, I read.

510
00:51:14,360 --> 00:51:18,680
And you must be Ruby.
You have a very nice room.

511
00:51:22,720 --> 00:51:26,080
You've made a wonderful home
for these children.

512
00:51:26,400 --> 00:51:28,880
-Thank you, Dr. Glass.
-Thank you.

513
00:51:32,400 --> 00:51:34,240
We'll see you out.

514
00:51:35,760 --> 00:51:39,200
You read? You lie.

515
00:51:39,760 --> 00:51:41,040
Guess who I learned from?

516
00:52:13,440 --> 00:52:14,760
Bye now.

517
00:52:43,000 --> 00:52:45,200
Why don't we order some dinner, hon?

518
00:52:58,520 --> 00:53:00,760
How do you like your new room?

519
00:53:02,480 --> 00:53:04,600
Couldn't have come at a better time.

520
00:53:28,400 --> 00:53:30,360
Come on, Mr. Begleiter.

521
00:53:51,720 --> 00:53:55,160
-Hello?
-Sorry to disturb you this late.

522
00:53:55,400 --> 00:53:59,520
But I found myself wondering,
"Where's the money?"

523
00:54:04,640 --> 00:54:06,200
You might as well know.

524
00:54:06,480 --> 00:54:11,040
Six months ago I took on a partner.
A silent partner and...

525
00:54:11,280 --> 00:54:15,160
...l recently found out
he was skimming cash.

526
00:54:16,000 --> 00:54:20,240
You've lost me. What does
this have to do with our loan?

527
00:54:22,280 --> 00:54:23,960
I'm waiting, Mr. Glass.

528
00:54:25,160 --> 00:54:28,960
-Mr. Glass, you still there?
-Yeah.

529
00:54:30,760 --> 00:54:33,960
He charged personal
expenses to the company.

530
00:54:34,200 --> 00:54:38,320
When I want a heartbreaking
human interest story...

531
00:54:38,560 --> 00:54:41,040
...I'll watch the news.

532
00:54:41,280 --> 00:54:45,760
Meanwhile, your payment's due
tomorrow, close of business.

533
00:54:46,320 --> 00:54:48,160
Do you fully understand me?

534
00:54:54,040 --> 00:54:55,520
Mr. Glass?

535
00:54:56,480 --> 00:54:58,400
I'm here.

536
00:55:00,000 --> 00:55:03,200
I'm seeking full restitution
from my partner.

537
00:55:03,480 --> 00:55:06,120
Plus I found a whole new
source of equity.

538
00:55:06,360 --> 00:55:08,680
My big, new, personal piggy bank.

539
00:55:09,000 --> 00:55:11,400
So you can expect another $30,000.

540
00:55:11,600 --> 00:55:16,080
That barely covers interest.
You need to pay off the principal.

541
00:55:16,360 --> 00:55:20,280
But I need some more time.
Not a lot more time.

542
00:55:20,520 --> 00:55:21,600
A week at the most.

543
00:55:21,840 --> 00:55:25,760
We'll give you two days,
because we like you.

544
00:55:26,000 --> 00:55:30,600
We'd hate for you to find
your beautiful house burnt down...

545
00:55:30,840 --> 00:55:33,160
...with your wife inside.

546
00:56:06,280 --> 00:56:07,360
Yeah?

547
00:56:13,480 --> 00:56:17,040
"I unfold a tale whose
word would harrow up thy soul...

548
00:56:17,280 --> 00:56:19,200
...freeze thy young blood...

549
00:56:19,440 --> 00:56:22,840
...make thy two eyes
start from their spheres...

550
00:56:23,080 --> 00:56:25,800
...and each hair to stand an end.

551
00:56:26,040 --> 00:56:28,040
If thou didst thy father love...

552
00:56:28,280 --> 00:56:32,880
...revenge his foul and unnatural
murder. Murder most foul...

553
00:56:33,160 --> 00:56:37,560
But this most foul,
strange, and unnatural...."

554
00:56:43,120 --> 00:56:44,120
Begleiter and Brice.

555
00:56:44,320 --> 00:56:48,520
-This is Ruby Baker for Mr. Begleiter.
-One moment.

556
00:56:52,160 --> 00:56:56,080
-Did you get my e-mail?
-No, Terry trashed my account.

557
00:56:56,920 --> 00:56:59,800
Or maybe the bill didn't get paid.

558
00:57:00,040 --> 00:57:02,360
Did you find out about the BMW?

559
00:57:02,600 --> 00:57:05,120
Right, the BMW.

560
00:57:05,360 --> 00:57:08,320
It was registered
to a business: G.T.I.

561
00:57:08,520 --> 00:57:10,680
Glass Transit Incorporated.

562
00:57:11,080 --> 00:57:14,280
-Terry's company.
-Now don't you get it?

563
00:57:15,920 --> 00:57:18,040
Ruby, please come with me.

564
00:57:20,240 --> 00:57:23,520
I have to call you back later.
Bye-bye.

565
00:57:25,120 --> 00:57:28,200
This is Miss Bassett,
our vice principal.

566
00:57:29,480 --> 00:57:30,440
Ruby.

567
00:57:30,920 --> 00:57:35,400
The paper you turned in to Mr. Kim,
that was your work, nobody helped?

568
00:57:35,600 --> 00:57:38,560
-No.
-Not even Harold Bloom?

569
00:57:39,440 --> 00:57:43,160
"Dance of contraries,"
didn't sound like a student.

570
00:57:43,440 --> 00:57:46,680
I found it and other phrases
in Mr. Bloom's book:

571
00:57:46,920 --> 00:57:49,520
Shakespeare:
The Invention of the Human.

572
00:57:49,760 --> 00:57:54,320
We were told there's a case of
plagiarism on your school record.

573
00:57:54,520 --> 00:57:57,960
You understand why we have to
take decisive action--

574
00:57:58,240 --> 00:57:59,560
You were told?

575
00:58:00,720 --> 00:58:03,280
-By who?
-That is hardly the issue here.

576
00:58:03,760 --> 00:58:07,400
This sort of cheating
has to have real consequences.

577
00:58:07,600 --> 00:58:09,600
We've spoken to your guardians.

578
00:58:11,400 --> 00:58:12,720
Of course you have.

579
00:58:12,960 --> 00:58:17,560
Frankly, we're not sure whether
you can continue at this school.

580
00:58:29,400 --> 00:58:30,520
Well?

581
00:58:31,280 --> 00:58:32,600
Why don't you ask Terry?

582
00:58:35,480 --> 00:58:39,040
Or maybe it's time you took
some responsibility.

583
00:58:41,200 --> 00:58:42,760
Maybe it's time.

584
00:59:24,840 --> 00:59:28,000
This is Jack Avery.
I'm out of the country...

585
00:59:28,240 --> 00:59:30,760
...but I'm checking my messages.

586
01:00:51,680 --> 01:00:53,200
Wake up.

587
01:00:57,400 --> 01:00:59,960
Don't make a sound.
Get dressed. We're gonna go.

588
01:01:00,200 --> 01:01:03,240
-Where? With who?
-Away with me.

589
01:01:04,040 --> 01:01:08,560
-Quit it! You're looking!
-Like there's something to see.

590
01:01:09,120 --> 01:01:12,240
It's raining. I was sleeping.
I don't wanna go.

591
01:01:12,480 --> 01:01:13,880
It'll be really fun.

592
01:01:16,840 --> 01:01:20,400
They're giving away
Dragon Ball Z at Blockbuster.

593
01:01:20,600 --> 01:01:22,400
We can go and avoid the rush.

594
01:01:24,600 --> 01:01:25,720
Really?

595
01:01:39,160 --> 01:01:40,160
Close the door.

596
01:01:50,480 --> 01:01:52,160
What if they find out?

597
01:01:53,440 --> 01:01:56,040
I'll take the blame.
Get in the car.

598
01:02:11,160 --> 01:02:13,360
You don't know what you're doing.

599
01:02:31,240 --> 01:02:32,600
Wanna slow down a little?

600
01:02:32,840 --> 01:02:36,000
One thing I learned from Terry:
Buckle up.

601
01:02:55,520 --> 01:02:58,600
-Terry's gonna kill you!
-Maybe so.

602
01:03:06,520 --> 01:03:08,280
Turn that off.

603
01:03:10,040 --> 01:03:11,040
Turn that shit off!

604
01:03:16,520 --> 01:03:17,680
Look out!

605
01:03:23,840 --> 01:03:25,920
You almost creamed that guy!

606
01:03:27,360 --> 01:03:28,600
Right. Turn it off!

607
01:03:42,880 --> 01:03:45,240
-I wanna go back.
-We're not.

608
01:03:45,480 --> 01:03:48,320
-What do you mean?
-Figure it out.

609
01:03:48,520 --> 01:03:52,320
We have to! You tricked me
and now I'm in trouble.

610
01:03:52,520 --> 01:03:54,960
-The Glasses tricked you.
-What?

611
01:03:55,200 --> 01:03:57,320
Did not. They're sleeping.

612
01:04:13,040 --> 01:04:17,800
They were gonna send me away
and you'd stay home with them.

613
01:04:18,040 --> 01:04:20,400
I like Terry. I like Erin.

614
01:04:20,600 --> 01:04:23,920
You like the shit they buy you.
You couldn't see it.

615
01:04:24,200 --> 01:04:26,360
They made you lie
to that social worker.

616
01:04:26,560 --> 01:04:29,480
I didn't know she was
a social worker.

617
01:04:29,680 --> 01:04:31,800
You didn't wanna lose
your Nintendo.

618
01:04:34,520 --> 01:04:36,560
They bought you off.

619
01:04:37,520 --> 01:04:41,400
-Where are you taking us?
-The point was to get away.

620
01:04:46,160 --> 01:04:47,480
Crap.

621
01:05:00,160 --> 01:05:02,200
Don't say anything stupid.

622
01:05:05,920 --> 01:05:07,680
The highway is closed.

623
01:05:07,920 --> 01:05:11,680
There's a mudslide.
You need to use Malibu Canyon....

624
01:05:15,880 --> 01:05:19,200
-Can I see your driver's license?
-My license?

625
01:05:19,440 --> 01:05:23,000
-And your registration too.
-It's....

626
01:05:24,280 --> 01:05:26,400
It's over there in all my stuff.

627
01:05:29,960 --> 01:05:32,160
I think I saw it over here.

628
01:05:35,640 --> 01:05:38,520
Pull onto the shoulder and step out.

629
01:05:44,840 --> 01:05:46,120
Officer!

630
01:05:49,320 --> 01:05:51,000
These are my kids.

631
01:05:51,680 --> 01:05:53,120
Terry Glass, Glass Transit.

632
01:05:53,400 --> 01:05:56,840
-We loaned you limos for the parade.
-How are you?

633
01:05:59,480 --> 01:06:01,080
Rhett, poor baby! Come with me.

634
01:06:01,400 --> 01:06:04,280
We have a behavior problem
back at home.

635
01:06:04,520 --> 01:06:08,200
Your sister's going through
a hard time right now.

636
01:06:08,480 --> 01:06:11,720
-You know, teenage-girl stuff.
-Got you.

637
01:06:12,680 --> 01:06:13,720
Good luck.

638
01:06:23,360 --> 01:06:25,000
Move over.

639
01:06:27,240 --> 01:06:29,400
-You can turn around here.
-Thanks.

640
01:06:47,000 --> 01:06:48,640
Don't you have anything to say to me?

641
01:06:52,600 --> 01:06:53,880
You killed my parents.

642
01:06:55,720 --> 01:06:57,760
That's insane and hurtful.

643
01:06:58,520 --> 01:07:03,360
You're threatened by your
business associates. I saw it.

644
01:07:03,560 --> 01:07:06,600
Like Erin said to me,
"We need your trust."

645
01:07:06,880 --> 01:07:09,440
You need my trust,
$4 million worth.

646
01:07:09,640 --> 01:07:12,960
I got a business.
My wife's a successful doctor.

647
01:07:13,240 --> 01:07:15,360
-I got a big, new--
-"Piggy bank."

648
01:07:19,000 --> 01:07:21,920
That's just words out of context.

649
01:07:22,200 --> 01:07:25,560
-What about the BMW my dad drove?
-What about it?!

650
01:07:28,360 --> 01:07:31,960
For their anniversary,
I lent them a Beemer...

651
01:07:32,200 --> 01:07:34,840
...so Dave wouldn't drive her
in that Saab...

652
01:07:35,080 --> 01:07:37,440
...which I repainted.

653
01:07:37,640 --> 01:07:39,400
No good deed goes unpunished.

654
01:07:39,640 --> 01:07:42,960
In your trashy mind,
you twisted that into--

655
01:07:43,480 --> 01:07:47,680
What do you think? Cut the steering,
stripped the brakes?

656
01:07:48,160 --> 01:07:49,120
Yeah.

657
01:07:49,320 --> 01:07:51,960
It's understandable,
basic psychology.

658
01:07:52,840 --> 01:07:55,080
You don't wanna blame your dad.

659
01:07:55,360 --> 01:07:57,880
That he had too much booze
that night.

660
01:07:58,080 --> 01:08:00,480
Then you'd
ask why your mom and dad...

661
01:08:00,760 --> 01:08:04,640
...hit the bottle.
Whose behavior drove them to drink?

662
01:08:23,680 --> 01:08:25,480
Get this straight.

663
01:08:26,520 --> 01:08:29,480
You and Rhett are mine.

664
01:08:42,240 --> 01:08:46,440
I suggest you forget your lurid,
adolescent fantasies and start--

665
01:08:52,000 --> 01:08:53,120
Help!

666
01:08:54,720 --> 01:08:57,920
-Let me go, bastard!
-Calm down, little girl!

667
01:09:04,480 --> 01:09:06,080
What's happening out there?

668
01:09:06,920 --> 01:09:08,920
Your sister is having a tantrum.

669
01:09:09,120 --> 01:09:12,120
Come on. Come back to bed.

670
01:09:13,920 --> 01:09:16,440
Let me go! Get off!

671
01:09:18,040 --> 01:09:19,040
Let go!

672
01:09:22,440 --> 01:09:23,640
You...!

673
01:09:30,400 --> 01:09:32,200
Listen hard, Ruby.

674
01:09:32,520 --> 01:09:35,360
Anything happens to you,
we got Rhett...

675
01:09:35,520 --> 01:09:37,640
...and all we need is one child.

676
01:09:38,520 --> 01:09:42,600
Erin! Stop him, please!

677
01:09:42,880 --> 01:09:44,000
Erin!

678
01:09:47,160 --> 01:09:51,040
Please come help me, please!
He's not gonna hurt you!

679
01:09:52,120 --> 01:09:55,680
Erin, please don't! Erin, don't! No!

680
01:10:02,440 --> 01:10:03,920
Thank you for listening.

681
01:10:06,120 --> 01:10:10,880
You'll feel better now, Ruby.
Rest, relax.

682
01:10:28,680 --> 01:10:30,520
-Where to, ladies?
-The mall.

683
01:10:30,720 --> 01:10:33,080
Time-out.
Has anyone heard from Ruby?

684
01:10:33,280 --> 01:10:37,440
-Me? Not for a month.
-Same. Won't even answer my e-mails.

685
01:10:37,680 --> 01:10:41,680
What up with Little Miss Malibu?
Too busy bodysurfing?

686
01:10:42,200 --> 01:10:44,600
Then we are too busy for her.

687
01:10:53,360 --> 01:10:56,760
-Hello?
-Where's the rest of our money?

688
01:10:57,600 --> 01:11:00,800
The bank sent me a check
with the wrong zip code.

689
01:11:01,080 --> 01:11:05,440
Some incompetent jerk at the bank
inverted the last digits!

690
01:11:05,680 --> 01:11:07,680
So I'll need another--

691
01:11:14,560 --> 01:11:18,040
We gotta expand the house,
a wing for the kids.

692
01:11:18,280 --> 01:11:23,040
Our little boy gets bigger every day,
and the girl is a teen.

693
01:11:23,360 --> 01:11:25,280
I don't know if you have kids....

694
01:11:27,800 --> 01:11:32,600
Anyway, construction costs
in Malibu are off the charts.

695
01:11:32,840 --> 01:11:35,240
I'm estimating a quarter million.

696
01:11:36,200 --> 01:11:40,680
We'll need to see blueprints.
There's an approval process.

697
01:11:40,960 --> 01:11:43,680
You can't get them
without an architect.

698
01:11:43,960 --> 01:11:47,160
Mine wants a cash down payment.
He's in demand.

699
01:11:48,320 --> 01:11:51,000
I believe we advanced you...

700
01:11:52,600 --> 01:11:56,160
...$30,000 for that purpose
just last month.

701
01:11:56,440 --> 01:12:00,600
But that was for a room,
before I realized I needed a wing.

702
01:12:00,920 --> 01:12:04,640
Isn't a guardian supposed to
keep the kids comfortable?

703
01:12:06,680 --> 01:12:08,120
Here's the trust.

704
01:12:08,360 --> 01:12:11,680
It authorizes me to use money
to enlarge the house.

705
01:12:12,600 --> 01:12:16,480
And guardians aren't supposed
to suffer economically...

706
01:12:16,760 --> 01:12:21,080
...in fulfilling their obligations?
I'm paying two tuitions.

707
01:12:21,320 --> 01:12:26,120
I employ a nanny. The kids see
therapists to deal with the tragedy.

708
01:12:26,400 --> 01:12:29,320
I plan trips to broaden
their horizons...

709
01:12:29,560 --> 01:12:33,440
... and it's like a root canal
when I need reimbursement.

710
01:12:40,200 --> 01:12:43,680
-Where'd you get it?
-You faxed it to us last week.

711
01:12:44,160 --> 01:12:49,080
I'm surprised to hear you have
both children at Westcott.

712
01:12:51,400 --> 01:12:56,440
Did I say Westcott? We changed our
minds about it. It's too glitzy.

713
01:12:57,640 --> 01:13:02,400
-We gotta do what's best for them.
-Isn't that the truth?

714
01:13:03,000 --> 01:13:06,040
Thank you for waiting.
I'll take your order.

715
01:13:06,360 --> 01:13:09,640
I need five dozen
1 0cc syringes fentanyl...

716
01:13:09,920 --> 01:13:13,280
...and I need two dozen
20cc syringes Demerol.

717
01:13:13,480 --> 01:13:16,160
We sent up 60 of fentanyl on Monday.

718
01:13:16,440 --> 01:13:20,520
I doubled the PCA infusion
rate of Demerol in six patients.

719
01:13:20,800 --> 01:13:22,120
Dr. Glass?

720
01:13:22,760 --> 01:13:24,920
I'm on the phone with the pharmacy.

721
01:13:25,120 --> 01:13:27,160
Dr. Wise wants to see you.

722
01:13:28,600 --> 01:13:30,360
The Medical Director.

723
01:13:49,640 --> 01:13:51,400
Wake up, Ruby.

724
01:13:52,440 --> 01:13:53,920
Sleeping Beauty.

725
01:14:03,520 --> 01:14:07,720
All you do is sleep. It scares me.

726
01:14:11,040 --> 01:14:15,200
So you're losing your medical license.
That's wonderful.

727
01:14:16,480 --> 01:14:20,680
-I have a sickness.
-Yeah, it's called self-pity.

728
01:14:21,560 --> 01:14:25,400
Complicated by being born
without a freaking backbone.

729
01:14:25,600 --> 01:14:27,880
So I'm weak, am l?

730
01:14:28,440 --> 01:14:29,880
Maybe I am.

731
01:14:30,840 --> 01:14:33,640
At least I'm not greedy
and reckless...

732
01:14:33,920 --> 01:14:36,360
...borrowing a million
from loan sharks--

733
01:14:36,640 --> 01:14:40,760
Which should've been paid off!
We had a good thing going...

734
01:14:41,080 --> 01:14:42,760
...till you put your hand in.

735
01:14:43,240 --> 01:14:46,120
A good thing? You son of a bitch!

736
01:14:46,400 --> 01:14:50,080
-I was a doctor!
-Yeah, but you became a junkie.

737
01:14:50,360 --> 01:14:54,280
Not until you did what you did.

738
01:14:54,560 --> 01:14:56,760
Where were you when I did it?

739
01:15:00,360 --> 01:15:05,080
Right. I saw an opportunity, Erin.

740
01:15:05,320 --> 01:15:08,120
I saw an opportunity and grabbed it.

741
01:15:08,320 --> 01:15:12,480
I had what you didn't.
I had the nerve, the will.

742
01:15:12,760 --> 01:15:15,800
Since nobody gave me
a chance, I took it.

743
01:15:16,040 --> 01:15:18,240
I'm not doing this anymore.

744
01:15:21,360 --> 01:15:23,280
It's already done.

745
01:15:23,760 --> 01:15:27,320
This is about containing the damage.
Understand?

746
01:15:29,600 --> 01:15:30,680
Good.

747
01:15:33,040 --> 01:15:36,080
You know we have to
get rid of the girl.

748
01:15:36,360 --> 01:15:38,440
Speaking of which, we're dry?

749
01:15:39,360 --> 01:15:44,280
There's nothing to take care of her,
so I'll get something.

750
01:15:46,080 --> 01:15:48,480
If I can't find drugs in L.A....

751
01:16:22,920 --> 01:16:24,200
Hi!

752
01:16:25,280 --> 01:16:28,600
Wave at the camera, Ruby.
Wave at the camera!

753
01:16:28,880 --> 01:16:30,480
They can't catch me!

754
01:16:31,520 --> 01:16:34,840
-Come in the water, Erin!
-Wait! I'm coming too!

755
01:16:43,600 --> 01:16:48,200
Spin me, Erin! Faster!
-Good girl.

756
01:17:43,920 --> 01:17:47,320
Rhett. Rhett, move away.

757
01:18:08,680 --> 01:18:11,440
Erin! It took some doing...

758
01:18:11,720 --> 01:18:14,680
...but I found some
pharmaceutical morphine.

759
01:18:17,440 --> 01:18:18,680
Erin?

760
01:18:41,320 --> 01:18:43,240
God, not now.

761
01:18:45,480 --> 01:18:46,520
Erin?

762
01:18:48,160 --> 01:18:49,360
Erin?

763
01:18:53,200 --> 01:18:56,240
1 875 Montego Canyon.

764
01:18:57,120 --> 01:18:59,240
I thought you'd wanna know.

765
01:19:06,440 --> 01:19:07,560
Ruby?

766
01:19:11,680 --> 01:19:12,920
Honey?

767
01:19:19,920 --> 01:19:23,080
Terry needs to talk to you kids.

768
01:20:55,680 --> 01:20:58,320
You kids are a handful,
you know that?

769
01:20:59,280 --> 01:21:02,960
Where's your sister?
Where's your damn sister?

770
01:21:16,400 --> 01:21:18,680
I should've put you here from day one.

771
01:22:24,080 --> 01:22:25,760
What's happening?

772
01:22:34,560 --> 01:22:35,640
He got the Jag.

773
01:22:51,240 --> 01:22:54,440
-He walked back in the house.
-Keep working.

774
01:23:23,760 --> 01:23:25,240
He's sleeping.

775
01:23:31,440 --> 01:23:35,480
He fell asleep.
There's gonna be a change of plans.

776
01:24:36,640 --> 01:24:38,320
Why would he do that?

777
01:24:39,440 --> 01:24:40,800
He's bombed!

778
01:24:41,000 --> 01:24:44,240
He finished a bottle of vodka.
It's right there.

779
01:24:47,840 --> 01:24:49,200
I see what's weird.

780
01:25:08,560 --> 01:25:10,160
Begleiter! What's going on?

781
01:25:10,400 --> 01:25:14,280
You ought to have your
wife take a look at that.

782
01:25:14,720 --> 01:25:18,560
-She's not home.
-Your office said you were home.

783
01:25:19,200 --> 01:25:22,480
I kept calling but nobody answered,
so here I am.

784
01:25:24,040 --> 01:25:27,760
The bank blocked your
guardianship account.

785
01:25:28,000 --> 01:25:30,960
The officer believes
there's malfeasance.

786
01:25:31,560 --> 01:25:33,160
The sons of bitches!

787
01:25:33,440 --> 01:25:35,520
I went out on a limb for you.

788
01:25:35,760 --> 01:25:38,640
I warned you about the girl's claims...

789
01:25:39,040 --> 01:25:43,280
...about her accusations, because I
trusted you, as did the Bakers.

790
01:25:43,520 --> 01:25:46,680
But if you've lied,
the courts will step in.

791
01:25:46,920 --> 01:25:51,000
If they take these children,
they have no place to go.

792
01:25:53,040 --> 01:25:55,160
He thought he was helping us.

793
01:26:09,520 --> 01:26:12,200
Mr. Glass, where are the children?

794
01:26:14,120 --> 01:26:17,440
At their music lessons.
Their piano lessons.

795
01:26:17,640 --> 01:26:20,320
Next, I'll have to buy
them a Steinway...

796
01:26:20,560 --> 01:26:24,440
...and the bank will say,
"Can't they play the kazoo?"

797
01:26:30,480 --> 01:26:31,920
Shit!

798
01:26:35,120 --> 01:26:36,280
That's my Testarossa.

799
01:26:36,520 --> 01:26:40,320
No, that's our Testarossa.
Until we get our money back.

800
01:26:40,520 --> 01:26:42,920
You planned to skip town today?

801
01:26:43,120 --> 01:26:45,320
Where'd you get that idea?

802
01:26:45,520 --> 01:26:49,160
-Your wife called us this morning.
-My wife?

803
01:26:51,520 --> 01:26:56,680
Before you leave, how about repaying
the loan in one lump cash sum?

804
01:26:57,120 --> 01:26:59,040
He doesn't have our money.

805
01:26:59,240 --> 01:27:01,880
-What's going on, Terry?
-Ask him.

806
01:27:02,160 --> 01:27:05,240
-Your partner?
-Bastard robbed me blind.

807
01:27:06,920 --> 01:27:09,960
-Oh, my God. I'm leaving.
-No, no, no.

808
01:27:11,040 --> 01:27:12,480
-You're not.
-Really?

809
01:27:12,680 --> 01:27:15,320
-We need an explanation.
-From me?

810
01:27:15,560 --> 01:27:17,320
I have nothing to do with this!

811
01:27:33,360 --> 01:27:36,240
-Nobody listens anymore.
-Are you happy, Terry?

812
01:27:36,800 --> 01:27:40,000
Feel good about that?
Terry, you're a troublemaker.

813
01:27:41,280 --> 01:27:45,920
-That took care of the problem.
-No. We'll discuss this in the car.

814
01:27:46,160 --> 01:27:47,880
There's nothing to discuss!

815
01:27:49,280 --> 01:27:52,040
Just walk like a man out to the Jag.

816
01:27:52,320 --> 01:27:54,680
That was the problem. You solved it.

817
01:27:55,520 --> 01:27:57,760
The rest is pure profit.

818
01:27:59,280 --> 01:28:00,480
Not the Jag. The Volvo.

819
01:28:02,640 --> 01:28:04,760
Wait here for a minute, okay?

820
01:28:09,680 --> 01:28:13,440
-Nice little drive in our car.
-No! Not in there!

821
01:28:13,640 --> 01:28:16,760
Not in there! No! Not in there!

822
01:28:17,040 --> 01:28:18,880
I don't even have the key!

823
01:28:19,120 --> 01:28:21,480
We got all the keys to all the cars.

824
01:28:21,760 --> 01:28:23,520
Take the Volvo, not the Jag!

825
01:28:24,040 --> 01:28:26,800
-Let's go!
-Okay, you win!

826
01:28:27,400 --> 01:28:29,360
-You win.
-It's over.

827
01:28:29,600 --> 01:28:32,200
Just please take the Volvo, okay?

828
01:28:32,480 --> 01:28:34,400
You're making this difficult.

829
01:28:34,720 --> 01:28:36,600
-Whatever.
-Take the Volvo.

830
01:28:36,960 --> 01:28:39,240
Brand loyalty. I like that.

831
01:28:50,160 --> 01:28:51,600
That little bitch!

832
01:28:51,840 --> 01:28:55,120
You're some kind of joker.
We'll take the Jaguar.

833
01:28:55,400 --> 01:28:56,440
No!

834
01:29:53,120 --> 01:29:56,120
You haven't been
to our Tarzana office.

835
01:29:56,640 --> 01:29:59,120
We got a handball court and a sauna...

836
01:29:59,400 --> 01:30:03,120
...and way in the back we have
this special room.

837
01:30:04,240 --> 01:30:05,480
Totally soundproof.

838
01:30:20,000 --> 01:30:20,960
What the--?

839
01:30:30,160 --> 01:30:31,120
What the--?

840
01:31:17,680 --> 01:31:21,840
What'd you do to this car?!
What'd you do to this car?!

841
01:32:07,720 --> 01:32:10,000
Hi, you guys need some help?

842
01:32:11,920 --> 01:32:13,080
Yes.

843
01:32:39,880 --> 01:32:43,120
-Everything under control?
-We got it covered.

844
01:33:01,920 --> 01:33:03,080
Terry.

845
01:33:07,280 --> 01:33:09,480
You two kids stay in the car.

846
01:33:11,080 --> 01:33:14,600
I have a possible T.C.
Southbound, Malibu Canyon.

847
01:33:14,880 --> 01:33:17,840
-I'll be investigating.
-Copy that.

848
01:34:01,840 --> 01:34:03,240
I have a rollover T.C...

849
01:34:03,520 --> 01:34:06,960
...with one fatality.
I'll need two backup units.

850
01:34:12,480 --> 01:34:14,160
Ruby.

851
01:34:26,280 --> 01:34:27,600
It's okay.

852
01:34:28,160 --> 01:34:30,960
Ruby, go! Drive!

853
01:34:33,480 --> 01:34:36,840
-Where's the stupid key?!
-It's okay!

854
01:34:37,480 --> 01:34:41,280
We're gonna die here! Let's go!
Come on, find them!

855
01:34:42,440 --> 01:34:43,400
Ruby!

856
01:34:45,280 --> 01:34:46,800
I need your help.

857
01:34:47,560 --> 01:34:49,200
-He's getting closer!
-I got them!

858
01:34:49,480 --> 01:34:51,480
He's getting closer!

859
01:34:53,600 --> 01:34:55,200
Drive! Drive! Drive!

860
01:35:00,480 --> 01:35:02,160
Why are you stopping?!

861
01:35:06,640 --> 01:35:07,640
It's okay, honey.

862
01:35:08,320 --> 01:35:10,920
-Buckle up.
-What're you doing?!

863
01:35:12,960 --> 01:35:15,160
-All's forgiven.
-What're you doing?

864
01:35:58,240 --> 01:36:02,040
You kids okay?
Go back and wait by my car.

865
01:36:44,680 --> 01:36:47,520
Things will get easier from here on.

866
01:36:49,120 --> 01:36:50,800
They already have.

867
01:36:52,840 --> 01:36:54,440
Let's go home.

